title: Grateful Dead Live at Folsom Field, U. of Colorado on 1980-06-07
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil-> El Paso-> Mama Tried, Ramble On Rose, Passenger, Far From Me, Minglewood Blues, Loser, Feel Like A Stranger, Deal

Set 2

Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Althea, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E:Alabama Getaway-> E: One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Bl

Official 15th Anniversary celebration Other artist(s): Warren Zevon.

reviews.review_text: - The presence of Cipollina notwithstanding, a pretty substandard show.

iffy the jam out of sailor / saint is real hot, but the rest of the show is not...

FWIW I thought this was the best of the AUD tapes available for this date. this show is definitely in need of a soundboard though

It was a fun time     I like to download shows that i was at.  This was a hot day in Boulder.  We were all up there dancing and every once in a while would take a hose and spray it up in the air.  No it wasn't the greatest show i went to when i look at it.  Next day was another show and than Portland Ore and MT st Helen's show
